onverted mana cost of an object is the total amount of mana in its mana cost, regardless of color. See rule 203, \ldblquote Mana Cost and Color.\rdblquote \par }\pard\plain \s28\li400\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin400\itap0 \i\fs20\lang1033\cgrid {\b Example:}{ An Air Elemental has a mana cost of \{o3\}\{oU\}\{oU\} and a converted mana cost of 5.\par }\pard\plain \s27\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {\par }\pard\plain \s26\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {Copiable Values\par }\pard\plain \s27\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {An object\rquote s \ldblquote copiable values\rdblquote  are the values that are printed on the object, as modified by other copy effects, plus any values set for face-down spells or permanents. Other effects (including type-changing effects) and counters are not copied. See rules 503.2 and 503.3.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {Copy\par }\pard\plain \s27\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {A \ldblquote copy\rdblquote  of an object is an object whose copiable values have been set to those of the first object. See rule 503, \ldblquote Copying Objects.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s26\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {Cost\par }\pard\plain \s27\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\cgrid {Playing spells and activated abilities requires paying a cost. Most costs are paid in mana, but they may also include paying life, tapping or sacrificing permanents, discarding cards, and so on.\par      A player can\rquote t pay a cost unless he or she has the necessary resources to pay it fully. For example, 